  "why": "The paper goes beyond merely reporting failures: it analyzes patterns in where failures occur (by mutation type and over time), compares failure counts across multiple SUTs, and measures and reports false-positive rates via manual inspection. These analyses provide partial diagnostic insight (statistical/pattern-level characterization) into the conditions that induce failures (e.g., adding cars produces many more inconsistencies than recoloring, and higher-ranked SUTs sometimes show more inconsistencies). However, the paper does not trace failures to underlying model vulnerabilities (e.g., by analyzing training-data bias, identifying reliance on specific spurious features, or examining model internals such as neuron activations or coverage). Thus the work provides partial (pattern-level) diagnostics but not root-cause explanations linking failures to underlying model weaknesses.",
